      "action": "BUY",
      "entity": "THE BOEING COMPANY",
      "narrative": "# CORRUPTION BRIEF: THE BOEING COMPANY (BA)\n\n**Boeing has received two NASA contracts collectively valued at over $32.9 billion**, including the Space Launch System (SLS) core stage contract and the Lunar Gateway/Artemis-related agreements, making NASA one of Boeing's largest federal government clients alongside the Department of Defense. **Boeing's lobbying expenditures have consistently exceeded $15 million annually**, with documented contributions to members of the Senate Commerce Committee and House Armed Services Committee — the precise oversight bodies that authorize NASA and defense appropriations. **Federal procurement records show Boeing has received over $163 billion in government contracts since 2000**, a period during which the company faced concurrent Inspector General investigations, a 2021 DOJ deferred prosecution agreement over the 737 MAX, and ongoing GAO protests regarding contract award procedures. **Historically, Boeing has demonstrated a recurring pattern of regulatory capture**, including the FAA oversight failures documented in the 2020 House Transportation Committee report, and revolving-door employment of former defense and NASA officials in senior procurement-facing roles.\n\n---\n\n*Sources: USASpending.gov, OpenSecrets.org, DOJ Public Records, House Transportation Committee Final Report (Sept. 2020), GAO Contract Protest Database, SEC EDGAR*\n\n**Note:** This brief reflects documented public record. Signal scoring reflects contract volume correlation, not confirmed insider activity."
